The paper proposes a deep-learning approach for determining the 6D relative pose of Autonomous Underwater Vehicles (AUV) from a single image. This involves localization of robots in an underwater environment, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO). The approach uses image translation and deep learning techniques for pose estimation, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a simulation environment for training, which could be related to computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the application of the proposed technique is for multi-robot tasks, which could be related to systems and control (cs.SY).
